article.description: La'Tangela Atkinson scored 17 points, Kenya McBee had 14 points and nine rebounds, and No. 12 North Carolina beat South Carolina State 90-51 Friday night.
article.headline: Tar Heels shot 77 percent in 2nd half
article.linkText: No. 12 UNC dominates boards, SC State for win
article.story:
CHAPEL HILL, N.C. (AP) -- La'Tangela Atkinson scored 17 points,
Kenya McBee had 14 points and nine rebounds, and No. 12 North
Carolina beat South Carolina State 90-51 Friday night.

Nikita Bell added 12 points and Jessica Sell 11 for the Tar
Heels (6-0) Nicole Rhem scored 21 points for South Carolina State
(1-3).

North Carolina held the Lady Bulldogs to 28 percent first-half
shooting on the way to a 49-25 lead at the break. The Tar Heels
were 13-for-17 (77 percent) from the floor in the second half.

Melaney Denson added 14 points and Latasha Cook 10 for South
Carolina State.

Sell made all three of her 3-point attempts for the Tar Heels,
who dominated the boards 50-31.
